executeRequest

public static java.lang.Object executeRequest(HttpUriRequest req)
                                       throws java.io.IOException
Used internally to execute the Apache HTTP Components request and pull out either JSON or a raw response. A Map is always returned that has either the real data from your call, or an "ERROR" or "RESULT" key. If "ERROR" is given then you have "RESULT" as the body of the HTTP response for informational purposes. If you have "RESULT" only then the body couldn't be parsed as JSON and is just a raw string.

Throws:
java.io.IOException
